(firstQuint)Deep Brain Stimulation for the Treatment of Obesity in Patients With Prader-Willi Syndrome.

 The purpose of this study is to investigate the safety and efficacy of deep brain stimulation in obese patients with Prader Willi syndrome refractory to conventional treatment.

 Patients will be implanted with hypothalamic DBS electrodes.

 Calorimetric and anthropometric measures, body mass index, side effects, neuropsychiatric evaluations will be carried out at 6 months for measuring primary and secondary outcome.

 Side effects will be monitored at 1, 3, 6 and 12 months following surgery.

